{
  "stem": "2460.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were about 18 or 20 young men and young women.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we went into a small room from the Haganah.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there was a table.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "On the table was the Taanach, with the map of Israeli and a revolver.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we went in one by one, and we had to swear on the Haganah of Israel.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But before we did this, the man said that if somebody wants-- if somebody doesn't feel right, he can leave, and he doesn't have to swear to be a soldier of the Israeli army.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You know, it was very primitive, like a partisan-like.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was still illegal.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, when we left Czechoslovakia, I left like a Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My name was Chaim Bugarski.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my papers were all there, like I was 19 years old.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we-- when we crossed the train too from Czechoslovakia to Germany, the border patrol came and checked the papers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he saw that in my luggage was things wrapped in Czechoslovakian paper.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He says, how come that is-- you're Hungarian, and you have Czechoslovakian newspaper?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said, because I spent a couple days in Czechoslovakia, so I took the newspaper.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, he knew exactly who we are.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But this was the-- I want to ask you something that might not be clear for people in the future.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If the Jewish community-- if the Jews already knew that the State of Israel would be established, why were they pushing for immigration when it was still illegal?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "What was the purpose to get all these people, young people, to Palestine if there was a hope that the State of Israel would be established?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Why were people risking their lives fighting the British?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This is something that may not be clear, especially to students.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
